cs.CC, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CG. 

The paper deals with the undecidability of a puzzle game, which is a topic that falls under computational complexity (cs.CC). The game involves generating and manipulating rooms, which suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of treasure chests and jars also implies a data structures (cs.DS) component. Finally, the game is 2D and involves platforming, which could be seen as related to computer graphics (cs.CG).
